sonetMIB.description: The MIB module to describe SONET/SDH interfaces objects.

sonetMediumEntry.name: sonetMediumEntry
sonetMediumEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Medium table.

sonetMediumType.name: sonetMediumType
sonetMediumType.description: This variable identifies whether a SONET or a SDH signal is used across this interface.

sonetMediumTimeElapsed.name: sonetMediumTimeElapsed
sonetMediumTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement period.

sonetMediumValidIntervals.name: sonetMediumValidIntervals
sonetMediumValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data has been stored. A SONET device must support at least n intervals. The minimum value of n is 4. The default of n is 32. The maximum value of n is 96. The value of this object will be n unless the device was brought online within the last (nx15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the device has been online.

sonetMediumLineCoding.name: sonetMediumLineCoding
sonetMediumLineCoding.description: This variable describes the line coding for this interface. The B3ZS and CMI are used for electrical SONET/SDH signals (STS-1 and STS-3). The Non-Return to Zero (NRZ) and the Return to Zero are used for optical SONET/SDH signals.

sonetMediumLineType.name: sonetMediumLineType
sonetMediumLineType.description: This variable describes the line type for this interface. The line types are Short and Long Range Single Mode fiber or Multi-Mode fiber interfaces, and coax and UTP for electrical interfaces. The value sonetOther should be used when the Line Type is not one of the listed values.

sonetMediumCircuitIdentifier.name: sonetMediumCircuitIdentifier
sonetMediumCircuitIdentifier.description: This variable contains the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

sonetSectionCurrentEntry.name: sonetSectionCurrentEntry
sonetSectionCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Section Current table.

sonetSectionCurrentStatus.name: sonetSectionCurrentStatus
sonetSectionCurrentStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the interface. The sonetSectionCurrentStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. The sonetSectionNoDefect should be set if and only if no other flag is set. The various bit positions are: 1 sonetSectionNoDefect 2 sonetSectionLOS 4 sonetSectionLOF

sonetSectionCurrentESs.name: sonetSectionCurrentESs
sonetSectionCurrentESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds encountered by a SONET/SDH Section in the current 15 minute interval.

sonetSectionCurrentSESs.name: sonetSectionCurrentSESs

sonetSectionIntervalNumber.name: sonetSectionIntervalNumber
sonetSectionIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, which identifies the interval for which the set of statistics is available. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1.

sonetSectionIntervalESs.name: sonetSectionIntervalESs
sonetSectionIntervalESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds encountered by a SONET/SDH Section in a particular 15-minute interval in the past 24 hours.

sonetPathCurrentWidth.name: sonetPathCurrentWidth
sonetPathCurrentWidth.description: A value that indicates the type of the SONET/SDH Path. For SONET, the assigned types are the STS-Nc SPEs, where N = 1, 3, 12, 24, and 48. STS-1 is equal to 51.84 Mbps. For SDH, the assigned types are the STM-Nc VCs, where N = 1, 4, and 16.

The various bit positions are: 1 sonetPathNoDefect 2 sonetPathSTSLOP 4 sonetPathSTSAIS 8 sonetPathSTSRDI 16 sonetPathUnequipped 32 sonetPathSignalLabelMismatch

sonetVTCurrentWidth.name: sonetVTCurrentWidth
sonetVTCurrentWidth.description: A value that indicates the type of the SONET VT and SDH VC. Assigned widths are VT1.5/VC11, VT2/VC12, VT3, VT6/VC2, and VT6c.

sonetVTCurrentStatus.name: sonetVTCurrentStatus
sonetVTCurrentStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the interface. The sonetVTCurrentStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects and failures simultaneously. The sonetVTNoDefect should be set if and only if no other flag is set. The various bit positions are: 1 sonetVTNoDefect 2 sonetVTLOP 4 sonetVTPathAIS 8 sonetVTPathRDI 16 sonetVTPathRFI 32 sonetVTUnequipped 64 sonetVTSignalLabelMismatch
